unittitle_ssm: International Brotherhood of Painters and Allied Trades, Local 490 Records
abstract_ssm: The International Brotherhood of Painters, Local 490 (more commonly known as the Paperhangers Local), were established in 1864, located in New York City. The union was most active in the first half of the 20th century. The collection is made up of ledgers, minute books, financial records, and other related materials.
